# Documentation Guidelines

## Description
This rule provides standards for creating and maintaining documentation for the Solana Trading Simulator project. Follow these guidelines to ensure comprehensive, accurate, and user-friendly documentation.

## Patterns
- **/*.md
- **/*.rst
- **/docs/**/*

## General Documentation Principles
- Keep documentation current and accurate
- Document all major components and features
- Use clear, concise language
- Include code examples where appropriate
- Provide both high-level overviews and detailed guidance
- Update documentation when code changes

## Project Documentation Structure
- Follow the established documentation structure:
  - docs/README.md: Documentation overview and table of contents
  - docs/index.md: Complete user guide
  - docs/firebase_*.md: Firebase setup and data schema
  - docs/simulation_guide.md: Guide for running simulations
  - docs/buy_simulator.md & docs/sell_simulator.md: Strategy documentation

## Component Documentation
- Document the purpose and functionality of each component
- Include parameter descriptions and default values
- Explain trading strategy logic in detail
- Document Firebase integration thoroughly
- Include examples of component usage

## Code Examples
- Provide well-commented code examples
- Show complete, working examples
- Include example outputs where appropriate
- Reference examples from the examples/ directory
- Explain parameter choices in examples

## Command Line Interface Documentation
- Document all CLI commands and parameters
- Include example command lines for common tasks
- Document command output formats
- Explain error messages and troubleshooting

## Firebase Documentation
- Maintain accurate Firebase data schema documentation
- Document collection and field structures
- Include field types and descriptions
- Document data validation and processing requirements
- Explain common challenges and solutions

## Strategy Documentation
- Explain the logic behind trading strategies
- Document entry and exit conditions
- Explain parameter impact on strategy performance
- Include backtest results for different parameter sets
- Document strategy limitations and assumptions

## Visualization Documentation
- Document chart creation and interpretation
- Explain metrics and calculations
- Provide sample visualization outputs
- Document color schemes and annotations

## Troubleshooting Documentation
- Include common issues and solutions
- Document error messages and their meaning
- Provide guidance for debugging
- Include FAQ sections for common questions
- Document known limitations
